^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 227 - January 15, 2001 ^*N }
^-
We left you hanging last week as we were unable to find a "clearly correct approach" to the deal that was presented. We received about a dozen e-mails from our readers with suggestions concerning the best line of play in ^*BDeal for the Week 226^*N. Most of these e-mails contained some good points, but only France's ^*BVincent Labbe^*N was able to provide us with a sense of closure on this difficult deal. Vincent works for ^*BLe Bridgeur^*N magazine, one of the most respected bridge publications in the world, so it is no surprise that he was able to find the line that he did.

We will present a summary of Vincent's approach soon, but make sure you keep reading after that! Later in this week's deal is the answer to a suit combination problem that we posed to those of you who receive ^*BThe Deal of the Week^*N by e-mail. Finally we will present a deal that ^*BBill Barkley^*N played very well. Thanks to Bill for sending us this deal and for all of our readers that took the trouble to e-mail us their thoughts concerning last week's deal.

